# ReturnGuard AI Architecture Reference

## 1. Entity-Relationship (ER) Diagram

```mermaid
erDiagram
    user ||--o{ Transaction : "makes"
    user ||--o| UserFeature : "has"
    user ||--o{ RiskScore : "receives"
    
    Transaction {
        Int id PK
        String user_id FK
        String order_id UK
        String item_id
        Float item_price
        DateTime purchase_date
        DateTime return_date "nullable"
        String return_reason "nullable"
        Float refund_amount
        String payment_method "nullable"
        String receipt_id "nullable"
    }

    UserFeature {
        String user_id PK
        Int total_orders
        Int total_returns
        Float return_rate
        Float user_avg_gap
        Int duplicate_receipts
        Float full_refund_ratio
        Int high_value_returns
        Int returns_last_7_days
        Float avg_weekly_returns
        Float f_return "Feature F1"
        Float f_wardrobe "Feature F2"
        Float f_timing "Feature F3"
        Float f_receipt "Feature F4"
        Float f_refund "Feature F5"
        Float f_value "Feature F6"
        Float f_burst "Feature F7"
        DateTime last_updated
    }

    RiskScore {
        Int id PK
        String user_id FK
        String order_id "nullable"
        Float score
        String level "Normal | Moderate | Extreme"
        String status "Pending | Handled"
        String explanation
        DateTime created_at
    }

    PlatformBaseline {
        Int id PK "Always 1"
        Float platform_avg_return_rate
        Float platform_avg_gap
        Float platform_std_gap
        Float high_value_threshold
        DateTime last_updated
    }
```

---

## 2. Database Schema (Prisma / SQL)

The backend natively uses `Prisma` connected to a SQLite database. Here is the relational schema breakdown:

### Table: `Transaction`
Stores Raw CSV order/return telemetry.
*   `id` (Int, Auto-Increment, **Primary Key**)
*   `user_id` (String, Indexed)
*   `order_id` (String, **Unique**)
*   `item_id` (String, Nullable)
*   `purchase_date` (DateTime)
*   `return_date` (DateTime, Nullable)
*   `return_reason` (String, Nullable)
*   `item_price` (Float)
*   `refund_amount` (Float, Default: 0)
*   `payment_method` (String, Nullable)
*   `receipt_id` (String, Nullable)

### Table: [UserFeature](file:///Users/brak/Desktop/hackathn%20copy%202/server/src/services/features.js#63-165)
Houses the algorithmic calculation outputs per user.
*   `user_id` (String, **Primary Key**)
*   `total_orders`, `total_returns`, `return_rate` (Aggregates)
*   `user_avg_gap`, `duplicate_receipts`, `full_refund_ratio`, `high_value_returns` (Metadata)
*   `returns_last_7_days`, `avg_weekly_returns` (Time-series info)
*   `f_return`, `f_wardrobe`, `f_timing`, `f_receipt`,  `f_refund`, `f_value`, `f_burst` (F1-F7 ML Scaled Tensors in `[0,1]`)
*   `last_updated` (DateTime)

### Table: [RiskScore](file:///Users/brak/Desktop/hackathn%20copy%202/server/src/services/scoring.js#3-109)
Contains the generated fraud flags per transaction/user execution event.
*   `id` (Int, Auto-Increment, **Primary Key**)
*   `user_id` (String, FK, Indexed)
*   `order_id` (String, FK, Indexed)
*   `score` (Float, `0-100` Scale)
*   `level` (String, Enum: `Normal`, `Moderate`, `Extreme`)
*   `status` (String, Enum: `Pending`, `Handled`)
*   `explanation` (String, Generated LLM string)
*   `created_at` (DateTime)

### Table: [PlatformBaseline](file:///Users/brak/Desktop/hackathn%20copy%202/server/src/services/features.js#1-62)
A Singleton table storing ecosystem-level statistical benchmarks calculated recursively across all users.
*   `id` (Int, **Primary Key = 1**)
*   `platform_avg_return_rate` (Float, dynamically buffered safely)
*   `platform_avg_gap` (Float)
*   `platform_std_gap` (Float)
*   `high_value_threshold` (Float)

---

## 3. API Structure (Node.js/Express REST)

All routes are prefixed with `/api`.

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **POST** | `/api/transactions/upload` | **(Ingestion)** `multipart/form-data` upload accepting the CSV. Clears database rows, dynamically maps legacy (`order_value`) & new headers, triggers UserFeature calculations, stores RiskScores, and validates fraud. |
| **GET** | `/api/transactions` | **(Listing)** Returns a paginated JSON block of the last `100` raw transactions for rendering table history. |
| **GET** | `/api/metrics/summary` | **(Analytics)** Returns high level KPIs: `total_transactions`, `return_rate`, `average_risk_score`, and `high_risk_count`. Rendered directly into the Dashboard stat cards. |
| **GET** | `/api/fraud/alerts` | **(Alert Engine)** Retrieves the top `20` RiskScores dynamically sorted by `{ score: 'desc' }` that have `status: 'Pending'`. These map visually to the red/yellow alerts sidebar. |
| **GET** | `/api/risk/patterns` | **(Intelligence)** Aggregates and counts specific threat `explanation` strings attached to Moderate/Extreme alerts to show systemic attack vectors in the bottom-right Dashboard card. |
| **GET** | `/api/users/:user_id/risk` | **(Detail)** Requests a real-time recalculation of a specific user's [UserFeature](file:///Users/brak/Desktop/hackathn%20copy%202/server/src/services/features.js#63-165) F1-F7 profile and returns their singular risk assessment. |
| **POST** | `/api/transactions/:order_id/approve` | **(Resolution)** Manual Analyst Override. Flips a specific RiskScore `status` from `Pending` -> `Handled` and wipes the severity to `Normal`. |
| **POST** | `/api/users/:user_id/blacklist` | **(Resolution)** Heavy Override. Sweeps all RiskScores for the `userId`, forcing them all to `Extreme` severity, locking down the account. |
